result.execSummary:
The defendant Jesse Wayland Wahsquonaikezhik was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal 4th+), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Jesse Wayland Wahsquonaikezhik in court with attorney Tina F. Gouty-Yellow.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 2:14 PM. State - believes it is resolved, refers to defense counsel. State - plead to #1 and #2 as alleged with count #1 being a $300.00 fine plus costs and count #2 being court costs only, dismiss and read in count #3. Gouty-Yellow and defendant agree. Court dismisses and reads in count #3. Defendant pleads G to counts #1 and #2 as alleged. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his constitutional rights by entering his plea and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State - follow joint recommendation. Gouty-Yellow - follow joint recommendation. Defendant withholds comment. Court sentences the defendant to the following: count #1 - $300.00 fine plus costs and surcharges totalling $831.00 - 60 DTP/CO, count #2 - court costs only ($443.00) - 60 DTP/CO, submit DNA sample with expunction rights given, right to appeal, adjourned.
Final pre-trial on November 9, 2016 at 02:15 pm.

Defendant Jesse Wayland Wahsquonaikezhik in court with attorney Tina F. Gouty-Yellow and appears telephonically.  Defendant Jesse Wayland Wahsquonaikezhik in custody and appears via video from FOSO.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 10:16 AM. Court asks the defendant why he was not in Court yesterday. Gouty-Yellow tries to explain. Court wants to hear it from the defendant. Defendant responds, stated he was taking care of his appointments for his court date. Gouty-Yellow stated that she believes her client was confused and does not believe that he had a ride to Court. State received a fax from defense counsel that the defendant has signed the state's settlement recommendation so believes the defendant will be accepting the offer. Gouty-Yellow agrees. Court gives warning regarding appearing telephonically in the future without Court's approval. Court sets for FPT on 11/9/16. Gouty-Yellow is available that day but states that the defendant would lose his job if he has to remain in jail until then. State does not want that to happen, is OK with a $500.00 signature bond. Gouty-Yellow states that the defendant and her will ride together. Court - bond - continues as was previously set, quash the warrant.  Final pre-trial scheduled for November 9, 2016 at 02:15 pm.
From Attorney Gouty-Yellow requesting hearing and to appear via telephone for that hearing.
Return on warrant on November 4, 2016 at 10:00 am.

Attorney Tina F. Gouty-Yellow in court who appears telephoically.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 1:47 PM. State - scheduled for FPT. Court asks the attorney why her client is not here. Gouty-Yellow does not know why, she had instructed him to either appear in person or in her office and he did not. Court issues bench warrant, body or $1500.00. Gouty-Yellow asks if the court can call the case once/if he appears or is arrested. Court - once he has been picked up on the warrant, Court will schedule it for a hearing. Gouty-Yellow states that the defendant will be accepting the offer. State puts offer on record - plead to count #1 as alleged with $300.00 fine plus costs and pleading to either count #2 or #3 and dismiss the other count.
Final pre-trial on November 2, 2016 at 01:45 pm.
